    <body>
      <pb n="1082"/>
      <cb n="1"/>
      <salute rend="indent">
        <lb/>Mr <hi rend="sc">Urban</hi>, </salute>
      <dateline rend="align-right"><hi rend="italic">Nov.</hi> 3. </dateline>
      <p>
        <lb/><hi rend="dc(2)">I</hi>F the following remedy, which I have <lb/>known do good, ſhould
        give a Me- <lb/>dical Sufferer any relief, it will give me <lb/>great pleaſure. </p>
      <p rend="indent">
        <lb/>Take of a ſtrong infuſion or decoction <lb/>of linſeed, bruiſed, four ounces, ſtrain
        it, <lb/>and add of Venice treacle two drams, for <lb/>a gliſter, to be injected warm at
        night, <lb/>going to bed, and repeated for ſome <lb/>time: if he is of opinion he receives
        any <lb/>benefit, he may add half a dram of the <lb/>Th. for three or four times. </p>
      <signed rend="indent">
        <lb/>Yours, &amp;c. <hi rend="sc align-right">Meanwell. </hi>
      </signed>
    </body>
